dc_title_s: A plain map for the geographical game of Asia, Africa, America, and newly discovered islands: according to the method of the Abbé Gaultier.
dc_creator_sm: Gaultier, abbé (Aloisius Edouard Camille), 1746?-1818.,David Rumsey Collection.,Cartography Associates.
dc_description_s: Relief shown pictorially. Outline map showing continents, rivers, mountains, etc. Prime meridian: Ferro. 1 map: hand col.; 31 x 39 cm. This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
